# Template SCSS

Entry: `scss/master.scss` (imports theme, menu, offcanvas, animation, responsive, etc.).

## Rules

- Write new styles in `scss/`, not compiled `css/` (generated / often gitignored).
- Import new partials from `master.scss` (or an existing imported partial).
- Use Bootstrap 5 variables/mixins and Helix preset vars (`$bg_color`, `$link_color`, … from `$theme->getSCSSVariables()`).
- Preset colors live in `presets.scss` / runtime `add_scss('presets', ...)`.
- Prefer Bootstrap utilities in markup; keep SCSS scoped to avoid global clashes.
- Site-specific extras: `scss/custom.scss` or `css/custom.css` — do not fork `theme.scss` lightly.

## Compile path

`$theme->add_scss('master', $scssVars, 'template')` → `scssphp` → `css/` + cache under `cache/com_templates/templates/{template}/`.

```scss
// ✅ Use variables / nesting
.sp-page-title {
  background: $bg_color;
  a { color: $link_color; }
}

// ❌ Avoid dumping unscoped raw CSS that bypasses the pipeline
```
